==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flair
<hw>Flair</hw> <pr>(fl⟦acir⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>flaire</ets>odor, fr. OF. & F. <ets>flair</ets>, fr. OF.
<ets>flairier</ets>, F. <ets>flairer</ets>, to smell, LL.
<ets>flagrare</ets> for L. <ets>fragrare</ets>. See
<er>Flagrant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Smell; odor.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sense of smell; scent; fig., discriminating
sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A talent or ability, especially an intuitive one
that makes performance of a task appear easy; an intuitive appreciation;
a knack; <as>as, she has a <ex>flair</ex> for acting</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An attractive way of performing a task;
style.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flake</ent>⟦br⟧
